FBIS3-60859 "jptot001__l94107" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Hijackers Release One Boy LD2512171193 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1645 GMT 25 Dec 93 LD2512171193 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, 25 Dec (ITAR-TASS) -- After a tractor towed the helicopter with the terrorists and hostages to another runway at the Mineralnyye Vody airport today, another schoolboy, Zhenya Mezhuyev, was released. Thus two boys, the bus driver, and the helicopter's two pilots are still on board. The terrorists have declared they intend to leave Mineralnyye Vody when darkness sets in. [passage omitted] The terrorists promise to release the two boys remaining on board, having set as a condition that Valentina Petrenko, personal envoy of the Russian foreign minister, should be taken on board. [passage omitted] It is not excluded that after flying to Baku the terrorists will try to land in the mountains where it is possible that accomplices await them.
